  "body": "### Component\n\nAnvil\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [ ] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (8fd5930 2022-12-15T00:04:21.124299862Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nanvil_revert doesn't revert the `block.timestamp` properly.\r\n\r\nMinimal code to replicate:\r\n\r\nTimeTest.sol:\r\n```\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.0;\r\n\r\ncontract TimeTest {\r\n    uint cnt;\r\n    \r\n    function doSomething() external {\r\n      cnt++;\r\n    }\r\n    function getBlockTime() external view returns (uint) {\r\n      return block.timestamp;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\nIn hardhat:\r\n```\r\n        const factory = await ethers.getContractFactory('TimeTest');\r\n        const tt = await (await factory.deploy()).deployed()\r\n\r\n        const timeBefore = await tt.getBlockTime()\r\n        console.log('timeBefore: ', timeBefore);\r\n\r\n        const snapshot = await network.provider.request({\r\n            method: 'anvil_snapshot',\r\n            params: [],\r\n        })\r\n     \r\n        await tt.doSomething()\r\n\r\n        await network.provider.request({\r\n            method: 'anvil_revert',\r\n            params: [snapshot],\r\n        });\r\n\r\n        const timeAfter = await tt.getBlockTime()\r\n        console.log('timeAfter: ', timeAfter);\r\n```\r\nResult:\r\n```\r\ntimeBefore:  BigNumber { value: \"1671117544\" }\r\ntimeAfter:  BigNumber { value: \"1671117545\" }\r\n```",
